video.title: Animaniacs
video.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot Warner flee the studio where they've been cooped up for decades and wreak havoc on the world around them.

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Scratchansniff recalls his first attempt to cure the crazy Warners, and sings with them. The Animaniacs crew enjoys a parody of “Goodnight, Moon.”
episodes.title: De-Zanitized / The Monkey Song / Nighty Night Toon

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot try to sell cookies to Albert Einstein, which may help him with his theory of relativity. The Brain is a quiz-show contestant.
episodes.title: Yakko's World / Cookies for Einstein / Win Big

episodes.synopsis: Trespassers Yakko, Wakko and Dot crash a private beach. Slappy Squirrel takes on a mean dog to get walnuts for Skippy.
episodes.title: HMS Yakko / Slappy Goes Walnuts / Yakko's Universe

episodes.synopsis: The artist Michelangelo hires Yakko, Wakko and Dot to help with the Sistine Chapel. The Goodfeathers recall when Squit joined the gang.
episodes.title: Hooked on a Ceiling / Goodfeathers: The Beginning

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Scratchansniff has the unenviable task of teaching manners to consummate oddballs Yakko, Wakko and Dot.
episodes.title: Taming of the Screwy

episodes.synopsis: Mr. Plotz accidentally hires the Warners as his temporary secretaries. A sticky lollipop sends Mindy on a high-flying adventure.
episodes.title: Flipper Parody Song / Temporary Insanity / Operation: Lollipop / What Are We?

episodes.synopsis: The show must go on when Yakko, Wakko and Dot evade capture by crashing a piano recital. Rita and Runt have their first encounter in a flashback.
episodes.title: Piano Rag / When Rita Met Runt

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot aim to indulge themselves at a candy store. Skippy takes Slappy to meet an actress in New Mexico.
episodes.title: Warner's Lot Song / The Big Candy Store / Bumbie's Mom

episodes.synopsis: The Warners scale the Himalayas to ask a wise llama a question, and the Brain travels to Switzerland to use a freeze ray on world leaders.
episodes.title: Wally Llama / Where Rodents Dare

episodes.synopsis: Yakko inherits a small but magical kingdom, which is lovely until a dictator shows up and declares war.
episodes.title: King Yakko

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot just may inspire the painter Pablo Picasso. Rita and Runt star in their very own production of “Les Miserables.”
episodes.title: No Pain, No Painting / Les Miseranimals

episodes.synopsis: In need of a garage, Wakko and his siblings head to a garage sale. The Goodfeather pigeons find themselves in their own “West Side Story.”
episodes.title: Garage Sale of the Century / West Side Pigeons

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wacko and Dot must audition for a movie in order to avoid capture. Skippy Squirrel journeys across California to deliver a letter.
episodes.title: Hello Nice Warners / La Behemoth / Little Old Slappy from Pasadena

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot take the case when Dr. Scratchansniff gets a parking ticket. Buttons looks over Mindy at a construction site.
episodes.title: La La Law / Cat on a Hot Steel Beam

episodes.synopsis: The fantastically weird Yakko, Wakko and Dot get beamed up by space aliens. Pinky and the Brain put on a deceptive radio play.
episodes.title: Space Probed / Battle for the Planet

episodes.synopsis: The gangs puts a strict new teacher through the wringer, Slappy Squirrel runs into trouble at an awards ceremony, and Wakko burps out a waltz.
episodes.title: Chalkboard Bungle / Hurray for Slappy / The Great Wakkorotti: The Master & His Music

episodes.synopsis: Sooty chimney sweeps Yakko, Wakko and Dot bother Beethoven while he’s composing his fifth symphony. Rita contends with a nasty violin maker.
episodes.title: Roll Over Beethoven / The Cat and the Fiddle

episodes.synopsis: Pinky and the Brain have a rough time stealing jewels from the Russian czar when they’re conditioned to have a certain Pavlovian response.
episodes.title: Pavlov's Mice / Chicken Booryshnikov / Nothing but the Tooth

episodes.synopsis: The Grim Reaper wants to claim Wakko after he eats too many Swedish meatballs. Gina Embryo tries to prevent the Hip Hippos from moving to the city.
episodes.title: Meatballs or Consequences / A Moving Experience

episodes.synopsis: A talking flame on a candlestick witnesses the writing of the Declaration of Independence. Chicken Boo is a brave frontiersman.
episodes.title: The Flame / Wakko's America Song / Davy Omelette / Four Score and Seven Migraines Ago

episodes.synopsis: When an insane director’s budget balloons, Mr. Plotz hires the Warners to out-crazy him. The Goodfeather pigeons pay homage to Alfred Hitchcock.
episodes.title: Hearts Of Twilight / The Boids

episodes.synopsis: God puts Slappy Squirrel in charge of the Garden of Eden. Yakko, Wakko and Dot annoy their fellow airplane passenger.
episodes.title: Guardin' the Garden / Plane Pals

episodes.synopsis: Through song, the gang reveals what’s in junk food. Later, Mindy enters an imperiled rainforest, and Pesto gets his head stuck in a six-pack ring.
episodes.title: Be Careful What You Eat / Up the Crazy River / Ta Da Dump, Ta Da Dump, Ta Da Dump Dump Dump

episodes.synopsis: Pinky and the Brain have their hearts set on gold when they visit Fort Knox. A moth and a butterfly make for unlikely lovebirds.
episodes.title: Opportunity Knox / Wings Take Heart

episodes.synopsis: The gang searches for a diamond necklace in an Agatha Christie-like mystery. Rita and Runt think Cleopatra’s palace is Sonny Bono’s house.
episodes.title: Hercule Yakko / Home on De-Nile / A Midsummer Night's Dream

episodes.synopsis: The animated siblings inject some life into an old movie theater, saunter into medieval Camelot and desperately search for a bathroom.
episodes.title: Babblin' Bijou / Potty Emergency / Sir Yaksalot

episodes.synopsis: Yakko hosts a game show in which Wakko bashes contestants over the head with a mallet. Slappy exposes her neighbor for who she really is.
episodes.title: You Risk Your Life / I Got Yer Can / Jockey for Position

episodes.synopsis: Captain Ahab finds some new shipmates in Yakko, Wakko and Dot. Mindy and her family are now cave people living in the Stone Age.
episodes.title: Moby or Not Moby / Mesozoic Mindy / The Good, the Boo and the Ugly

episodes.synopsis: The homeward-bound Warners decide to take a detour to Dracula’s castle. Rita and Runt are on the run from a mad scientist who wants Runt’s brain.
episodes.title: Draculee Draculaa / Phrankenrunt

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot take a trip to the underworld and annoy the heck out of the devil. A dorky werewolf tries to woo Minerva Mink.
episodes.title: Hot, Bothered and Bedeviled / Moon Over Minerva / Skullhead Boneyhands

episodes.synopsis: When an opera singer destroys the Warner siblings’ commemorative glass with her high notes, it’s time for revenge.
episodes.title: O Silly Mio / Puttin' on the Blitz / The Great Wakkorotti: The Summer Concert

episodes.synopsis: Dot and her brothers have a long conversation with the most boring man in the world, and Mindy goes to live in outer space with Buttons.
episodes.title: Chairman of the Bored / Astro-Buttons

episodes.synopsis: The Hip Hippos mistake Noah’s Ark for a posh cruise ship. Wakko has a headache because a cartoon is stuck in his ear.
episodes.title: Noah's Lark / The Big Kiss / Hiccup

episodes.synopsis: Wakko’s debilitating fear of clowns rears its ugly head. Brain poses as a country singer to hypnotize the world.
episodes.title: Clown and Out / Bubba Bo Bob Brain

episodes.synopsis: It’s a set of mixed-up stories: Rita eats Pinky, and Mindy is the Brain’s unlikely partner in attempted world domination.
episodes.title: In the Garden of Mindy / No Place Like Homeless / Katie Ka-Boo / The Baghdad Café

episodes.synopsis: Slappy Squirrel gets revenge on two critics who panned her cartoons. Yakko, Wakko and Dot make for three not-so-valiant musketeers.
episodes.title: Critical Condition / The Three Muska-Warners

episodes.synopsis: Carrier pigeons have an important role in World War I, the Warners make a mess of boot camp, and Chicken Boo is a Civil War general.
episodes.title: Dough Dough Boys / Boot Camping / General Boo-Regard

episodes.synopsis: Pinky and the Brain may have almost found the spell that will allow them to take over the world. They just need one more ingredient.
episodes.title: Spellbound

episodes.synopsis: When Rita finds abandoned kittens, they consider her their mother whether she likes it or not. Yakko plays Shakespeare with Mr. Skullhead.
episodes.title: Smitten with Kittens / Alas Poor Skullhead / White Gloves

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot drive a quiz-show host bonkers. The Brain hypnotizes the young viewers of a puppet show to be his minions in the future.
episodes.title: Fair Game / Puppet Rulers

episodes.synopsis: Yakko and his crazy siblings teach a rude news anchorman some manners, and a New York pigeon becomes a real raging bull.
episodes.title: Broadcast Nuisance / Raging Bird

episodes.synopsis: Two hip hippos seek adventure while a hapless naturalist tries to preserve them, and a simple woodchuck bites off more than he can chew in Hollywood.
episodes.title: Can't Buy a Thrill / Hollywoodchuck

episodes.synopsis: Runt the dimwitted dog is suddenly in charge of a rabbit farm. Dr. Scratchansniff is pestered by surveyors who ask him questions about George Wendt.
episodes.title: Survey Ladies / Of Nice and Men / What a Dump

episodes.synopsis: Yakko provides some useless facts, and the whole gang sings about senses. When it comes to love, the Brain must take pointers from Pinky.
episodes.title: The Senses Song / The World Can Wait / Kiki's Kitten

episodes.synopsis: When it comes time to refurbish Windsor Castle, the Warners help, and the queen’s not getting through it with her dignity intact.
episodes.title: Mary Tyler Dot Song / Windsor Hassle / And Justice for Slappy

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot are Native Americans who must protect their pet turkey from the Pilgrims. A baby bird thinks a stealth fighter is its mother.
episodes.title: Turkey Jerky / Wild Blue Yonder

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot run amok in a video store. Pinky and the Brain travel back to a prehistoric era.
episodes.title: Video Review / When Mice Ruled the Earth

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot cross some mobsters and sing about Lake Titicaca. A small boy tells the story of his friend’s cat eating a fish.
episodes.title: Mobster Mash / Lake Titicaca / Icebreakers

episodes.synopsis: In a new spin on a Christmas classic, not a creature is stirring, not even a Wakko. Elsewhere, Chicken Boo is a department store Santa Claus.
episodes.title: Twas the Day Before Christmas / Jingle Boo / The Holiday Concert / Toy Shop Terror / Yakko's Universe

episodes.synopsis: The zany trio offer their own gleefully maniacal spin on a Christmas classic. Later, they retell the story of the birth of Jesus.
episodes.title: A Christmas Plotz / Little Drummer Warners

episodes.synopsis: The weird and wacky Warners have to think on their feet when they encounter a giant. Slappy Squirrel faces off against Daniel Boone.
episodes.title: The Warners and the Beanstalk / Frontier Slappy

episodes.synopsis: Wakko and Dr. Scratchansniff get stuck in an elevator together. The Brain reenacts a famous commercial outtake from Orson Welles.
episodes.title: Ups And Downs / The Brave Little Trailer / Yes, Always

episodes.synopsis: Dr. Scratchansniff enjoys a hot date at the drive-in until the Warners show up. The Goodfeathers follow their girlfriends to the Grand Canyon.
episodes.title: Drive-Insane / Girlfeathers / I'm Cute

episodes.synopsis: The Brain tangles with the infamous Dr. Jekyll. A silly dog tries to get Minerva Mink’s pelt but falls for her in the process.
episodes.title: Brain Meets Brawn / Meet Minerva

episodes.synopsis: Yakko and the gang face a greedy prospector during the 1840s gold rush. Wrapping paper gets a poignant story. Dot looks for a quiet reading corner.
episodes.title: Gold Rush / A Gift of Gold / Dot's Quiet Time

episodes.synopsis: Brain’s new infomercial is in fact just a front for an attempt at world domination. Mindy chases a balloon in France, and Buttons must keep her safe.
episodes.title: Schnitzelbank / The Helpinki Formula / Le Boutons et le Ballon / Kung Boo

episodes.synopsis: The inimitably odd Yakko, Wakko and Dot parody World War II propaganda films. Wakko has a particularly strange new invention.
episodes.title: Of Course You Know, This Means Warners / Up a Tree / Wakko's Gizmo

episodes.synopsis: The Brain runs for president with less-than-honorable intentions. Skippy and Slappy brave a scary dog in order to get food.
episodes.title: Oh Oh Ethel / Meet John Brain / Smell Ya Later

episodes.synopsis: The Animaniacs star as pastry chefs in one their original shorts from 1929. Slappy and Skippy Squirrel wander into Woodstock in 1969.
episodes.title: Ragamuffins / Woodstock Slappy

episodes.synopsis: A William Shatner look-alike bogarts the karaoke machine. Pinky and the Brain make a sorry Batman and Robin. Chicken Boo is the next James Bond.
episodes.title: Karaoke Dokie / Cranial Crusader / The Chicken Who Loved Me

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot meet a goofy reptile who hosts a kids' show, Super Buttons comes to the rescue, and Katie takes her dad’s wheels for a spin.
episodes.title: Baloney and Kids / Super Buttons / The Driving Lesson

episodes.synopsis: Slappy and Skippy Squirrel run into some bad guys while trick-or-treating. Rita the cat is accused of witchcraft during the Salem Witch Trials.
episodes.title: Scare Happy Slappy / Witch One / MacBeth

episodes.synopsis: Things get hairy when Pesto watches his sister’s unhatched egg. Mindy and her family live far under the sea.
episodes.title: With Three You Get Eggroll / Mermaid Mindy / Katie Ka-Boom: Call Waiting

episodes.synopsis: The gang meets the obnoxious Elmyra from “Tiny Toon Adventures.” Walter Wolf sabotages Skippy Squirrel’s plastic surgery.
episodes.title: Lookit the Fuzzy Heads / No Face Like Home

episodes.synopsis: Yakko, Wakko and Dot do it “live” in this special episode that takes viewers behind the scenes and features guest spots by Daffy Duck and Bugs Bunny.
episodes.title: The Warners 65th Anniversary Special

episodes.synopsis: The Warners face a bridge troll; A clown-themed car lures Mindy onto the Indy 500 track; The Warners try to out-funny radio host Howie Tern.
episodes.title: Take My Siblings Please / The Mindy 500/Morning Malaise
We're No Pigeons / Whistle Stop Mindy / The Broken Date

episodes.synopsis: Pesto tries to sabotage his mother's upcoming marriage; the Goodfeathers and Girlfeathers star in a spoof of "Fiddler on the Roof."
episodes.title: Miami Mama-Mia / Pigeon on the Roof

episodes.synopsis: A feuding Yakko and Dot take a road trip; Pesto and Squit try to cheer up Bobby; Katie frets over a pimple; The Warners prove wrestling is fake.
episodes.title: I'm Mad! / Bad Mood Bobby / Katie Ka-Boom: The Blemish / Fake

episodes.synopsis: The Warners seek a sleuth's help in a scavenger hunt; Slappy attends Walter's funeral (or does he?); The siblings sing about the United Nations.
episodes.title: Deduces Wild / Rest in Pieces / U.N. Me

episodes.synopsis: An enormous bug demolishes the studio; Slappy and Skippy try to open a walnut; Wakko tries out a new funny face; The Warners sing about an earthquake.
episodes.title: Super Strong Warner Siblings / Nutcracker Slappy / Wakko's New Gookie / A Quake, a Quake!

episodes.synopsis: Yakko decodes Variety magazine headlines; Slappy and Skippy accidentally attend a Three Tenors concert; Wakko and Dr. Scratchansniff play bingo.
episodes.title: Variety Speak / Three Tenors and You're Out / Bingo / Finale

episodes.synopsis: Fans overwhelm the Warners on their way to a convention; Slappy's vacation plans conflict with filming a movie; The Warners address obsessed fans.
episodes.title: A Hard Day's Warners / Gimme a Break / The Please Please Please Get a Life Foundation

episodes.synopsis: The Warners spoof "The Lion King"; Yakko tries to sing the dictionary; Siblings get a visit from the Warners; Slappy and Skippy take an acting class.
episodes.title: The Tiger Prince / All the Words in the English Language / The Kid in the Lid / A Method to Her Madness

episodes.synopsis: The Warners walk off a cartoon; Buttons and Mindy spoof "The Wizard of Oz"; Pinky and the Brain run amok when the Warners abandon a second cartoon.
episodes.title: Gimme the Works / Buttons in Ows / Hercules Unwound

episodes.synopsis: The Warners protect a statue; The siblings get zapped into "Star Truck"; A game of go fish angers Wakko; Yakko sings about multiplication.
episodes.title: This Pun for Hire / Star Truck / Go Fish / Multiplication Song

episodes.synopsis: The Warners sing about the presidents; The Brain rewrites the Declaration of Independence; The Flame witness the writing of "Paul Revere's Ride."
episodes.title: The Presidents Song / Don't Tread on Us / The Flame Returns

episodes.synopsis: A singing nanny sparks a spoof of "The Sound of Music"; Chicken Boo is among the actors at a table read for a movie about the Flintstones.
episodes.title: The Sound of Warners / Yabba Dabba Boo

episodes.synopsis: Slappy adopts a little bird; A surprise guest is expected at the Warners' party; The Flame witnesses the writing of "The Star-Spangled Banner."
episodes.title: My Mother the Squirrel / The Party / Oh! Say Can You See / The Twelve Days of Christmas

episodes.synopsis: Dot and her brothers sabotage a musical; The Warners star in a Googi Goop cartoon; In a hot desert village, everyone's after Dot's water.
episodes.title: Dot's Entertainment / The Girl with the Googily Goop / Gunga Dot

episodes.synopsis: Slappy coaches soccer; Katie Kaboom clashes with her parents over clothes; The Warners spoof "2001: A Space Odyssey"; Network censors pay a visit.
episodes.title: Soccer Coach Slappy / Belly Button Blues / Our Final Space Cartoon, We Promise / Valuable Lesson

episodes.synopsis: Wakko's song only has two notes; Yakko sings an ode to the Panama Canal; Wakko serenades Hello Nurse; The Warners sing about their wrap party.
episodes.title: Wakko's Two-Note Song / Panama Canal/Hello Nurse Song / The Big Wrap Party Tonight

episodes.synopsis: When his Aunt Slappy requires treatment for watching too many trashy talk shows, Skippy moves her into a home for retired cartoon characters.
episodes.title: One Flew over the Cuckoo Clock

episodes.synopsis: In a spoof of "Beauty and the Beast," Dot plays the heroine; Chicken Boo parodies "Forrest Gump"; The siblings reinterpret a classic Christmas carol.
episodes.title: Cutie and the Beast / Boo Happens / Noel

episodes.synopsis: Dot stars in a parody of Disney's "Pocahontas"; The Goodfeathers exact operatic revenge on Mr. Plotz; Yakko makes Wakko the star of "Casey at the Bat."
episodes.title: Jokahontas / Boids On The Hood / Mighty Wakko At The Bat

episodes.synopsis: The Warners try to win a humanitarian award; Zombies chase Mindy and Buttons in a graveyard; Yakko and Dot attempt to cure Wakko's hiccups.
episodes.title: A Very Very Very Very Special Show / Night of the Living Buttons / Soda Jerk

episodes.synopsis: The Warners and Agent 0007, Municipal Bond, face the ruthless Blowfinger; The trio joins Dr. Scratchansniff on vacation; Yakko sings about time zones.
episodes.title: From Burbank With Love / Anchors A-Warners / When You're Traveling From Nantucket

episodes.synopsis: The Warners search for Ernest Hemingway, who refuses to sign for a delivery; The Hippos parody "American Gladiators"; Pinky gets a spinoff series.
episodes.title: Papers for Pappa / Amazing Gladiators / Pinky and the Ralph

episodes.synopsis: Wakko stars in 10 short films; A cuckoo clock bird falls in love with a real bird; Chicken Boo devises a new TV schedule of bird-themed shows.
episodes.title: Ten Short Films About Wakko Warner / No Time For Love / The Boo Network

episodes.synopsis: Brain poses as a baby hippo to swindle a couple's fortune; Buttons watches over Mindy in Alice's Wonderland; Ralph accidentally marries Chicken Boo.
episodes.title: Pitter Patter Of Little Feet / Mindy In Wonderland / Ralph's Wedding

episodes.synopsis: Lost at sea, the Warners find a message in a bottle. Plotz loans the characters out to other studios. The Warners and Mr. Skullhead sing about bones.
episodes.title: Moosage in a Bottle / Back in Style / Bones in the Body

episodes.synopsis: Wakko is chased by something scary. The whole gang performs a dance and song about Dot. Skippy faces off against Duke, a school bully.
episodes.title: It / Dot: The Macadamia Nut / A Bully For Skippy

episodes.synopsis: Snow inherits a magic mirror. The Warners move in with some pals. The Warners sing about Attila the Hun. Chicken Boo becomes a superhero sidekick.
episodes.title: Cute First / Acquaintances / Here Comes Attila / Boo Wonder

episodes.synopsis: The Warners pitch a script idea to Thaddeus Plotz but quickly discover that getting a movie made in Hollywood isn't as easy as it looks.
episodes.title: Hooray for North Hollywood: Part 1

episodes.synopsis: After they get a director interested in their script while mingling at a Hollywood party, the Warners' movie is made and becomes a blockbuster hit.
episodes.title: Hooray for North Hollywood: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The Warners annoy their fellow car pool passengers. Slappy reunites with her former partner Suzy Squirrel to perform a sketch on a TV show.
episodes.title: The Carpool / Sunshine Squirrels

episodes.synopsis: Slappy's tree is cut down for Christmas. Chicken Boo tries to answer a riddle. Katie Ka-Boom is invited to the prom. Chicken Boo's quest continues.
episodes.title: The Christmas Tree / Punchline: Part 1 / Prom Night / Punchline: Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Famous magicians invite the Warners on stage to participate in their show. The Brain builds robots to take over the world but Pinky interferes.
episodes.title: Magic Time / The Brain's Apprentice

episodes.synopsis: A replacement conductor is driven crazy by the Warners. The series ends with a musical retrospective on moments from throughout the show's history.
episodes.title: The Scoring Session / The Animaniacs Suite
